  "lastReviewFeedback": "coderabbitai: **Actionable comments posted: 6**\n\n<details>\n<summary>🤖 Prompt for all review comments with AI agents</summary>\n\n```\nVerify each finding against the current code and only fix it if needed.\n\nInline comments:\nIn @.gitignore:\n- Around line 48-50: Remove the duplicate ignore entry for \"test-results/\" in\nthe .gitignore by keeping a single \"test-results/\" line and deleting the\nredundant occurrence so the pattern only appears once; search for the exact\nstring \"test-results/\" in the file and ensure only one entry remains to avoid\ndrift and confusion.\n\nIn `@packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-icon/hx-icon.stories.ts`:\n- Around line 196-199: The story for the hx-icon decorative example uses\nhardcoded inline style values (e.g., gap: 0.5rem, implicit sizes and colors)\nwhich violates the project's theming rules; update the inline style blocks in\nthe hx-icon story (the example rendering the <hx-icon name=${args.name}\nhx-size=${args.size} ...> and the other instances noted at 225-245 and 277-288)\nto use token-backed CSS custom properties prefixed with --hx- (for spacing,\ncolor, size) instead of literal values so the story respects the --hx-* theming\ntokens used across the library.\n\nIn `@packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-icon/hx-icon.styles.ts`:\n- Around line 8-9: The styles currently use rem literals as fallbacks (e.g.,\nwidth/height: var(--hx-icon-size, var(--hx-size-6, 1.5rem))) which violates the\ntoken-only rule; remove the hardcoded rem fallbacks and use token-only cascades\ninstead (for example replace any var(--hx-..., var(--hx-size-..., <rem>))\npatterns with var(--hx-..., var(--hx-size-...))). Update all occurrences\nreferenced (the width/height lines and the other instances at the same pattern\non lines noted) so every fallback chain only references design tokens like\n--hx-icon-size and --hx-size-*, no literal units.\n\nIn `@packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-icon/hx-icon.test.ts`:\n- Around line 236-237: Replace the fixed 50ms setTimeout sleeps in the tes",
